# M3 typography (required)

All text must use the [Material Design 3 type scale](https://m3.material.io/styles/typography/type-scale-tokens).

## How to size text

1. **Prefer semantic HTML** — `h1`–`h6`, `p`, `label`, `button`, `nav a`, etc. Base styles in `app/globals.css` apply the correct M3 role automatically.
2. **Or** `import { type } from "@/lib/typography"` and use `type.bodyLarge`, `type.headlineLarge`, etc.
3. **Or** use `components/ui/typography.tsx` (`SectionHeading`, `Prose`, `Eyebrow`, …).
4. **Or** apply a `.type-*` utility class directly (`type-title-large`, `type-body-medium`, …).

## Forbidden

- Tailwind default sizes: `text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg`, `text-xl`, `text-2xl`, …
- Arbitrary sizes: `text-[14px]`, `text-[1.125rem]`
- Responsive font-size hacks: `md:text-3xl`, `lg:text-5xl`

## Role reference

| Token | Use for |
|-------|---------|
| `display-large` | Home hero title only |
| `display-small` | Page titles (`h1`) |
| `headline-large` | Section titles (`h2`) |
| `title-large` | Subsections, card titles (`h3`), lead copy |
| `body-large` | Default body (`p`, `li`) |
| `body-medium` | Secondary body, captions |
| `body-small` | Fine print (`small`) |
| `label-large` | Buttons, nav links, form labels |

Tokens and defaults live in `app/globals.css`. ESLint flags non-M3 text size classes.
